----------------------------------------
Installation instructions for RestFrames
----------------------------------------

'Executive Summary'
===================

RestFrames can be configured, built and installed using the standard sequence

    %> ./configure [options]
    %> make
    %> make install

'The Knitty-Gritty'
===================

There are myriad configuration options, a list of which can
be obtained by typing 

    %> ./configure --help

Install location
----------------

In particular: the default installation location for the package 
(when typing 'make install') is '/usr/local' -- if a user does not 
have permission to write there the 'make install' step will fail. In order to 
specify an install location, users should add the '--prefix' option to the 
'./configure' step:

    %> ./configure --prefix=MY_INSTALL_PATH

The install location path must be absolute. There are several different 
things installed at this location:

    MY_INSTALL_PATH/lib : compiled RestFrames libraries and rootmap file
    MY_INSTALL_PATH/include/RestFrames : library headers
    MY_INSTALL_PATH/libexec : scripts for setting environmental variables
    MY_INSTALL_PATH/bin : restframes-config executable   

Compiling against RestFrames library
------------------------------------

The 'restframes-config' executable can return compiler flags for linking 
against the RestFrames library. For example, if MY_INSTALL_PATH/bin is in a 
user's path then programs depending on the RestFrames library can be 
compiled by typing:

    %> g++ myprogram.C `restframes-config --cxxflags --libs` -o myprogram

Compiler options
----------------

Users can sepcify which C++ compiler to use when building the RestFrames 
library at the './configure' step:

    %> ./configure CXX=myCPPcompiler

Users can specify particular C++ compiler flags at the './configure' step:

    %> ./configure CXXFLAGS=flags